## AI Capabilities

### Image Generation
- Seamless text-to-image pipeline powered by DALL-E models.
- Support for customizable styling rules, aspect ratios, and resolutions.
- High-fidelity visual generation optimized for immediate download.

### Advanced Image Editing
- One-click background separation with pixel-edge precision.
- Intelligently context-aware object removal and image touch-ups.
- Designed to allow stable file processing.

### Creative Content Generation
- Complete article drafting equipped with customizable tone and structural control.
- Catchy, algorithmic blog title generation built to maximize user click-through rates.
- Embedded SEO optimization and topical keyword suggestions.

### Structural Document Processing
- Deep parsing of text structures from uploaded PDF resume documents.
- Automated resume score cards outlining exact structural strengths.
- Precision skills gap analysis coupled with actionable career improvement metrics.

---

## API Endpoints

### AI Service Routes (/api/ai)
- POST /generate-image : Handles text prompt processing to deliver newly generated images.
- POST /remove-background : Receives file payloads to isolate primary subjects from backgrounds.
- POST /remove-object : Identifies coordinates or target items to clean from images.
- POST /write-article : Generates curated text copy based on user parameters.
- POST /generate-titles : Returns multiple variations of engaging content titles.
- POST /review-resume : Extracts PDF information to output structural critiques and grades.

### User and Community Routes (/api/users)
- GET /profile : Fetches the current authenticated user's profile metadata.
- POST /creations : Persists a successfully generated AI asset to the user's private gallery.
- GET /creations : Pulls the full history of creations associated with the active account.
- GET /community : References all publicly shared community creations for display.

---

## Deployment Guide

### Frontend Deployment (Vercel)
Connect your GitHub repository directly to Vercel. Set the root directory configuration to point to the client folder, include your environment variables, and trigger a build deployment.

### Backend Deployment (Render or Vercel)
Deploy your server folder to an environment host capable of continuous Node.js runtime operations. Ensure all environment secrets matching your database, OpenAI, Cloudinary, and Clerk settings are updated in your provider dashboard.

### Database Hosting (Neon)
Create a serverless PostgreSQL cluster instance directly on Neon (https://neon.tech/) and paste the provided connection string inside your backend environmental parameters.

